[commands]
check_smtp=$USER1$/check_smtp -H $HOSTADDRESS$
check_smtp_time=$USER1$/check_smtp -H $HOSTADDRESS$ -w $ARG1$ -c $ARG2$
[name]
check_smtp

[info]
Checks status of a SMTP server.
[why]
To see status of your SMTP mailserver.
[how]
Connects to a SMTP server and checks status. Lets you specify expected responce string. You can also run a command and specify thresholds on responstime.
[platforms]
Not platform dependent.


